The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                ICSE and ISC 2010 will begin on March 3, the Council for Indian School Certificate Examinations, which conducts the examinations, announced on Wednesday.     A German tourist was found unconscious on the Bibhuti Express at Howrah station by RPF personnel at 12.45pm on Wednesday. David Pitman, 20, said he lost consciousness after accepting tea from two co-passengers. He told police his luggage, containing clothes, a camera, his passport and bank cards, were missing. He was admitted to Howrah District Hospital.     Motorcyclist Tanmoy Santra, 35, was run over on Hasnabad Main Road on Wednesday morning by a speeding lorry. The Basirhat resident was taken to a local hospital, where he was declared dead. The lorry driver fled with the vehicle.     Six taxi drivers who were arrested on Tuesday for attacking the office of a private vehicle testing centre at Salt Lake stadium were remanded in judicial custody for three days on Wednesday. A group of taxi drivers had allegedly damaged office property accusing the centre of delay in checking taxi meters.     A 40-year-old unidentified man was seriously injured after being hit by a car on Narkeldanga Main Road on Wednesday afternoon. Police rushed him to Calcutta Medical College and arrested the driver and impounded the car.     The body of an unidentified man in his 50s was found near Bamungachhi RRI cabin in Howrah on Wednesday morning. A GRP officer said an unreserved Howrah-to-Dibrugarh train ticket was found on on the body, which was sent for post-mortem.     A clash between two groups disrupted traffic on Narkeldanga Main Road for 30 minutes on Wednesday evening. Police brought the situation under control. The reason for the clash is not known yet.     An unidentified person in his 40s was crushed under the wheels of a lorry near the Calcutta Leather Complex at Bantala, on the southern city fringes, on Wednesday afternoon. He was taken to NRS hospital, where he was declared dead on arrival. Police seized the truck but the driver fled.                                                                                                                                                  
